Name: SimpleDate
Description: A single point in time. If a duration is expressed as a SimpleDate it is defining a period of time without a designated Start or End date.

Name: HistoricalDate
Description: A simple date expressed in a historical date format, including a specification of the date format and calendar used.

Name: StartDate
Description: Start of a date range. If there is a start date with no end date provided, this implies that the end date is unknown but that the date being recorded is not just a simple date but a range of unknown duration.

Name: HistoricalStartDate
Description: A start date expressed in a historical date format, including a specification of the date format and calendar used.

Name: EndDate
Description: End of a date range with a known start date.

Name: HistoricalEndDate
Description: An end date expressed in a historical date format, including a specification of the date format and calendar used.

Name: Cycle
Description: Use to indicate occurrence of this range within a series of ranges as an integer identifying the cycle, i.e. the 4th wave of a data collection cycle would have 4.
